Overview
========

sps (which stands for "sps spins") is a simple command-line utility which
reads from standard input and shows an ASCII art spinner.

Credits and Legal Information
=============================

sps is free and unencumbered software released under the terms of the MIT
license; see COPYING for the license text. For a list of its authors and
contributors, see AUTHORS.

The ASCII art logo at the top was made using FIGlet (http://www.figlet.org/).
